item.title: Compute potential energy due to gravity

material.mattext: How much potential energy, in kilojoules, does a `m` kilogram object have that is `h` meters above the surface of the earth? Take the surface of the earth as the reference height.
How much work, in joules, does a `F` newton force that is horizontally oriented (i.e. along the x-axis) do if the object is displaced `d` meters horizontally, and `h` meters vertically?
How much power, in watts, does a force have if it can deliver `W` joules in `t` seconds?
